    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Sure. I'm creating a filterable list of house designs which includes filtering by attributes like square footage, price, number of bedrooms and number of bathrooms. A design might have multiple variants like \"with garage\" or \"with double master suite\" which could specify different values for any of the attributes. A record in algolia represents the base model and all of its variants. So if the base model has 3 bedrooms and one of its variants, \"with double master suite\", adds an additional bedroom then that record can have 3-4 bedrooms. ",
