    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@mvanlonden The way I understand what you're trying to do is that you need to let the user enter one value per attributeName. And the composition of all of them form a Range. \r\n\r\nThat's why I was wondering if using a connectRange per attributeName where the min === max wouldn't do the tricks. \r\n\r\n```js\r\n<InstantSearch...>\r\n   <ConnectedRange attributeName=\"xxx\"/> //render only one input\r\n   <ConnectedRange attributeName=\"yyy\"/> //render only one input\r\n   ...\r\n</InstantSearch>\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I'm wrong about your use case maybe a small mock-up of the UI and interaction would hep. ",
