  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "just returning to this @mthuret / @mvanlonden - I have a business use case here whereby we have a min and max occupancy of a trip.. e.g. a trip can take between 4 and 10 people. I would like to have a simple input where I only show trips that can take 5 people.\r\n\r\nmy doc would look something like this:\r\n```` \r\n{\r\n   minPax: 4,\r\n   maxPax: 10\r\n}\r\n````\r\n\r\nWith the current `connectMultiRange` I can only perform a min/max comparison of a single attribute.\r\n\r\nA workaround might be to store all the valid group sizes, but seems a bit of a hack, and wouldn't work so well when the numbers get big.\r\n````\r\n{\r\n   pax: [4,5,6,7,8,9,10]\r\n}\r\n````",
