  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hello! We came across similar requirements recently. As far as I can see, using a `min` and a `max` attribute for range inputs is still not possible out of the box, right?\r\n\r\nWe're using the `vue-instantsearch` package and have a use case where one product requires a supplementary part of a certain size range. So for example product P needs a supplementary part with a size between 6.5 and 10 meters. A potential customer (website user) is looking for a product, that fits his needs (let's say 5 to 7 meters). As both ranges overlap (product capabilities and user requirements), product P would be a fit and should be displayed.\r\n\r\nIs it possible achieve this with `vue-instantsearch` without a complete Algolia component rewrite using a custom connector? What'd be the best approach?",
    "created_at": "2023-03-17T13:04:56Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5270#issuecomment-1473813668",
    "id": 1473813668,
